1999-01-01|1999-12-30.description: The first story arc of VERTIGO's gripping new series from the writer-artist team behind the acclaimed JONNY DOUBLE concludes. Simmering violence boils over into full-blown vengeance as Dizzy encounters "Mr. Shepard" , a mystery man with some insight into Agent Graves, and uncovers new information about her family's murderers that makes it even harder to make her decision. Just how far is Dizzy willing to go for a little bit of frontier justice?
1999-01-01|1999-12-30.name: 100 Bullets

1999-01-01|1999-12-30.description:
League Of Extraordinary Gentlemen

The league are on the look out for the cavorite and it leads them to the mysterious Doctor Fu Manchu. The Doctor is an evil man and the team has to really be stealthy to find and retrieve it. The team puts together a mission plan. Quatermain, Hawley Griffin and Mina Murray will infiltrate the inner layer. Meanwhile Doctor Jekyll is outside if needed.

Allan and the Sundered Veil

In Allan and the Sundred Veil, Allan and company are taken to the Spinx. The Spinx is the Time Traveler's hidden hide out. As the story goes they are not safe long as the four men are attacked by Morlocks.
1999-01-01|1999-12-30.name: Mysteries Of The East

1999-01-01|1999-12-30.description: Installments of all 4 TOMORROW STORIES features, each written by Alan Moore! Cobweb (illustrated by Melinda Gebbie) tracks a female fugitive through Indigo City's stygian depths; and a subway shoot-out 10 years past reveals "The Origin of Greyshirt" (illustrated by Rick Veitch)! Meanwhile, it's raining buttered cats in Queerwater Creek courtesy of Jack B. Quick (illustrated by Kevin Nowlan); and First American and U.S. Angel face juvenile crime head on in "Peril of the Pediatric Perpetrators" (illustrated by Jim Baikie)!

1999-01-01|1999-12-30.description: A gripping tale of supernatural menace and gripping horror concludes! The explosive ending finds Mace Black investigating an abandoned Louisiana orphanage. But these walls haven't contained human children for years. And if there is anything inside, it isn't looking for its Mommy. Don't miss the action as Mace and Proteus face off in a battle to the death!

1999-01-01|1999-12-30.description: What do young socialites do in a retirement village? They steer clearof the retirees, that's what! In this third chapter from Clover Honey creator, Rich Tommaso, gothic acquaintances Fran and Mel delve deeper into the strangeness of the middle class, finding that poodles are vicious animals and that suburbia is perhaps a breeding ground for the subhuman!
